  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel the <strong>potatoes</strong> and chop them into chunky chips, then add them to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 6-8 min or until slightly softened</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1663854389427-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1663854389427-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1663854389427-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1663854389427-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1663854389427-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]<strong> </span>vegetable oil</strong> to a deep baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 5 min or until the oil is hot</p><p>Peel and finely chop the <strong>shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>into wedges</p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped shallot </strong>and <strong>vegan mayo</strong> in a small bowl with the juice of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lemon</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>lemon mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1663854394337-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1663854394337-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1663854394337-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1663854394337-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1663854394337-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once done, drain the <strong>softened chunky chips</strong> and reserve the pot, give them a shake in the colander until the edges have fluffed up a little</p><p>Carefully remove the baking tray of <strong>hot vegetable oil</strong> from the oven and add the <strong>fluffed chunky chips</strong></p><p>Season them with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and turn them a few times until they're fully coated in the oil</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 30 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1663854400936-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1663854400936-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1663854400936-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
